To create a circular menu using JavaScript, you will typically use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript together. Here’s a simple example to construct a circular menu:

### HTML
```html
<div class="circle-menu">
    <div class="menu-item" style="--i:0;">1</div>
    <div class="menu-item" style="--i:1;">2</div>
    <div class="menu-item" style="--i:2;">3</div>
    <div class="menu-item" style="--i:3;">4</div>
</div>
```

### CSS
```css
.circle-menu {
    position: relative;
    width: 200px; /* Set width for the menu */
    height: 200px; /* Set height for the menu */
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin: auto;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
}

.menu-item {
    position: absolute;
    width: 50px; /* Size of the menu items */
    height: 50px; /* Size of the menu items */
    border: 2px solid #333;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    background-color: #fff;
}

.menu-item:hover {
    background-color: #e0e0e0;
}

.menu-item:nth-child(1) {
    transform: rotate(calc(var(--i) * 90deg)) translate(80px) rotate(calc(var(--i) * -90deg));
}
.menu-item:nth-child(2) {
    transform: rotate(calc(var(--i) * 90deg)) translate(80px) rotate(calc(var(--i) * -90deg));
}
.menu-item:nth-child(3) {
    transform: rotate(calc(var(--i) * 90deg)) translate(80px) rotate(calc(var(--i) * -90deg));
}
.menu-item:nth-child(4) {
    transform: rotate(calc(var(--i) * 90deg)) translate(80px) rotate(calc(var(--i) * -90deg));
}
```

