Certainly! Here’s a Perl script that converts all `.mp4` files in the current directory to `.mkv` using `ffmpeg`:

```perl
#!/usr/bin/perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use File::Glob qw(bsd_glob);

my @files = bsd_glob("*.mp4");

foreach my $file (@files) {
    my $output = $file;
    $output =~ s/\.mp4$/.mkv/;  # Change the extension to .mkv
    system("ffmpeg -i \"$file\" -c copy \"$output\"") == 0
        or warn "Failed to convert $file: $!";
}
```

Make sure to make the script executable and run it in the directory containing your `.mp4` files.

