To extract the first elements of `std::map` instances from a `std::array` of `std::map`, you can use a loop or standard algorithms. Here’s a simple way to do it using a loop:

```cpp
#include <array>
#include <map>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>

std::vector<uint32_t> extract_first_elements(const std::array<std::map<uint8_t, uint32_t>, N>& array) {
    std::vector<uint32_t> first_elements;

    for (const auto& m : array) {
        if (!m.empty()) {
            first_elements.push_back(m.begin()->second);
        }
    }

    return first_elements;
}
```

